This post breaks down how **SAP Service & Asset Manager (SSAM)** handles offline data, including the role of the offline OData store, delta tokens, and conflict resolution strategies. We also walk through a checklist for diagnosing sync failures.

## Key Concepts
- **Offline OData store**: local persistence, encryption, and dataset scoping.
- **Delta synchronization**: managing payload sizes and background sync windows.
- **Conflict handling**: last-write-wins vs. server-side rules.

## Troubleshooting Checklist
1. Verify OData metadata alignment between mobile client and backend.
2. Inspect device logs and payload sizes.
3. Check backend ICF services and CSRF/token configs.
4. Review user roles/authorizations and data filters.

## Practical Tips
- Keep initial download scope minimal for first-time sync.
- Use targeted reset for corrupt stores.
- Automate client log collection for L2/L3 support workflows.

> Note: Always validate against your SSAM version and backend stack.
